From 55d60f4776de1d10da7635ca64414e0594543726 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jarkko Sakkinen <jarkko.sakkinen@linux.intel.com>
Date: Sat, 30 Nov 2019 01:13:16 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 094/106] selftests/x86: Add a selftest for SGX

Add a selftest for SGX. It is a trivial test where a simple enclave
copies one 64-bit word of memory between two memory locations given to
the enclave as arguments. Use ENCLS[EENTER] to invoke the enclave.

Cc: linux-sgx@vger.kernel.org
Cc: linux-kselftest@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Jarkko Sakkinen <jarkko.sakkinen@linux.intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Pan, Kris <kris.pan@intel.com>
